    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<ol>\n<li>Go to the <em>menu</em> <code>Run</code>, and then to the <em>menu item</em> <code>Run Configurations</code>.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/170zO.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/170zO.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><p>In the <em>left panel</em>, go to <code>Java Application</code>, and then go to <code>Assertions</code>.</p></li>\n<li><p>In the <em>right panel</em>, choose the <em>tab</em> <code>Arguments</code>.</p></li>\n<li><p>Under the <em>field</em> for <code>VM arguments</code>, type <code>-ea</code> to enable assertions.</p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/x9TeH.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/x9TeH.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>Click on the <code>Apply</code> and then <code>Run</code> <em>button</em>.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>To globally set it as the <em>default for everything</em>:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Go to menu <code>Window</code> (if you are on Windows), or go to menu <code>Eclipse</code> (if you are on Mac). For Linux it might be something similar.</p></li>\n<li><p>Go to <code>Preferences</code>.</p></li>\n<li><p>Choose <code>Java</code>, and then <code>Installed JREs</code> from the <em>left panel</em>. </p></li>\n<li><p>Select your <em>JRE</em>, and then click the <code>Edit...</code> button in the <em>right panel</em>. </p></li>\n<li><p>In the <code>Default VM arguments</code> field, add <code>-ea</code>.</p></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
